&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Advert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a Registered looking for opportunities to develop your career within the Ambulatory and Day Treatment? Do you possess excellent communication skills, strong team working skills and can evidence the delivery of good patient care?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Then you can apply to join our Team at&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; the Ambulatory and Day Treatment Department, East and North Hertfordshire NHS Trust, QEII Hospital in Welwyn Garden City. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have patients requiring investigations and treatment such as OPAT, Blood transfusions, Wound care and more. We work closely with all specialties including, Medicine, Rheumatology and Oncology to name a few. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our services cover 08:00-18:30 on weekdays and 09:00-15:00 on weekends and bank holidays. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The department is predominantly Nurse led at weekends and bank holidays. During weekdays, we work closely with the Acute Medicine Team, therefore one years post registration experience would be an advantage.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As we grow and promote better patient care and experience in our new facilities, we are looking to recruit highly motivated, experienced and innovative staff who will embrace our exciting service developments, whilst providing the best care possible to our patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return, the Trust is committed to supporting and developing its’ staff so opportunities for training and other development activities will be provided.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Additional benefits include excellent annual leave entitlement, the NHS Pension Scheme, Accommodation, Shopping Discounts, Employee friendly benefits and further career development opportunities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NB - For International Applicants, please note that due to COVID19 we currently have put a hold on all international recruitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Internal Candidates - all internal move are currently on-hold&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aimée Saunders  Nurse Team Manager  aimee.saunders@nhs.net  01707247567&lt;/p&gt;
